e of the ruling ethos of our times: Eurocentrism - i.e., selfish and acquisitive materialism, of which the contemporary USA is the trend-setter and the unchallenged gold standard. DR. RAJANI KANTH has an MA in Social Anthropology from the Delhi School of Economics, India, and a PhD in Economics from the New School for Social Research, New York, USA. After serving as Economic Advisor to the UN in New York, he taught as University Professor, and is currently based at Harvard University.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access. Unless otherwise specified individually in the content, the work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives (CC BY-NC-ND) license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aAestheticsxEconomic aspectszUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aAlienation (Social psychology)zUnited StatesxHistory. 0aAmericanszUnited StatesxSocial life and customsy21st century. 0aCulturexEconomic aspectszUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aEconomic history and conditions. 0aPhilosophical anthropologyzUnited States. 0aSociology (General). 0aValueszUnited States. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economic History.2bisacsh  aPost-Humanism, American culture, Materialism-Amorality.0 cEPUBz97831104554650 cprintz978311045530440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110455311zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110455311zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110455311.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA